geo:siteIdentification.geo:notes: The GNSS reference mark consists of a brass plate with a forced centered stainless steel bolt embedded on top of a 2.0 m high concrete pier. The concrete pier is anchored to exposed bedrock by steel reinforcing rods.

geo:siteLocation.geo:notes: ALGO is a continuously tracking GNSS station and is part of the Canadian Active Control System (CACS). The station is colocated with the ALG2 GNSS station, the ALG3 GNSS station and the VLBI reference mark in Algonquin Park, Ontario. The Alqonguin Space Complex in Algonquin Park is located 160km west of Ottawa, Ontario.

geo:SurveyedLocalTie.geo:notes: Differential coordinates are from the GPS monument to the reference and other monuments. The components are parallel to the XYZ-Axes of the Global Geocentric Reference System ITRF (WGS-84).
